Styling Text and Fonts in CSS
CSS provides a wide range of properties to style text and fonts, allowing developers to control the appearance of headings, paragraphs, links, and other textual elements. Common text and font-related CSS properties include:

font-family: Defines the typeface for the text.
font-size: Specifies the size of the font.
font-weight: Sets the thickness or boldness of the font.
text-align: Aligns text horizontally (left, right, center, or justify).
color: Defines the color of the text.
text-decoration: Adds decorations like underlines to text (commonly used for links).
line-height: Controls the spacing between lines of text.
